Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 279378.77 and Total Revenue = 775598.77.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100 = (279378.77 ÷ 775598.77) × 100 ≈ 36.00%.

Step 2: Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –967147.02.
• From the balance sheet, Current Liabilities (Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable) = 7566370.00 + 38779.91 = 7605149.91.
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities ÷ Total Current Liabilities = (–967147.02 ÷ 7605149.91) ≈ –0.13.

Thus, the solution is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "36.00%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-0.13"
  }
}
